# GitHub Actions – Working with macOS Runners

macOS runners in GitHub Actions are Apple macOS-based virtual machines used to execute workflows.

They are mainly used for:

* iOS application builds
* macOS software development
* Xcode projects
* Swift applications
* Apple ecosystem testing

GitHub provides fully managed macOS virtual machines for workflow execution.

---

# What is a macOS Runner?

A macOS runner is:

> A macOS virtual machine used by GitHub Actions to run workflow jobs.

GitHub automatically:

* Creates macOS VM
* Executes workflow
* Removes VM after completion

---

# Common macOS Runner Labels

| Label        | Description         |
| ------------ | ------------------- |
| macos-latest | Latest stable macOS |
| macos-14     | macOS Sonoma        |
| macos-13     | macOS Ventura       |
| macos-12     | macOS Monterey      |

---

# Example

```yaml id="jlwm2d"
runs-on: macos-latest
```

---

# Why Use macOS Runners?

macOS runners are essential for Apple platform development.

---

# Common Use Cases

| Use Case               | Example             |
| ---------------------- | ------------------- |
| iOS app builds         | iPhone applications |
| macOS applications     | Desktop apps        |
| Swift projects         | Swift language      |
| Xcode builds           | Apple IDE workflows |
| Cross-platform testing | macOS compatibility |

---

# Workflow Lifecycle

```text id="jlwm86"
