# 6. Working with Xcode Projects

macOS runners are widely used for iOS/macOS builds.

---

# Example

```yaml id="jlwmsd"
name: iOS Build

on: push

jobs:
  build-ios:
    runs-on: macos-latest

    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Build iOS App
        run: |
          xcodebuild \
          -project MyApp.xcodeproj \
          -scheme MyApp \
          -sdk iphonesimulator \
          build
```

---

# What Happens?

| Step            | Purpose                |
| --------------- | ---------------------- |
| xcodebuild      | Builds iOS app         |
| iphonesimulator | Uses iOS simulator SDK |

